# Custos — Cursor Project Rules

`docs/agents.md` is the **canonical operating guide**, `docs/architecture.md` the
**project design & decisions**, `docs/spec.md` the **technical spec** (guardrail
parameters, contract interfaces, Anthropic API prompt + risk-signal schema), and
`docs/ui.md` the **UI/UX plan**. Read all four before acting. This rule restates
the non-negotiables.

**For PR reviews** (human or agentic): use `.cursor/rules/pr-review.mdc` — it
contains the full acceptance criteria, build/test commands, and the required review
output format.

## Project (one line)
**Custos** — an **AI risk-guardian real-yield account** on **Mantle** (chain ID
5000). Users deposit **USDC**; an AI agent (Anthropic API / Claude) earns
tokenized-Treasury (**USDY**) yield with an **Aave v3** USDC liquidity floor, and
**autonomously de-risks on-chain** into **AUSD**/USDC on RWA danger (depeg, oracle
staleness, issuer/regulatory shock), recording every decision **and its evidence**
on-chain under an **ERC-8004** identity. The verifiable autonomous defense — not the
swap-to-USDY — is the product.

## Non-negotiables
- **1delta = data + optional swap routing ONLY.** Never in the custody/execution
  path. The vault must never execute arbitrary third-party calldata. Execution
  happens only via our own adapters (`UsdyAdapter`, `AaveV3Adapter`, `AusdAdapter`)
  that call protocols/DEXs directly with on-chain `minOut`/guardrail checks.
- **Guardrails are final.** LLM proposes -> deterministic TS validator checks ->
  immutable on-chain guardrails are the backstop. The LLM may only **tighten**
  risk, never loosen it (see `docs/spec.md` section 3). Shared constants between
  `Guardrails.sol` and the TS validator live in `packages/shared`.
- **AI only where it beats an algorithm.** Yield math, peg/oracle/liquidity/
  execution stay deterministic. LLM is used only for: unstructured->structured RWA
  risk signals, written rationale, novel-event judgment, conversational UX. No
  AI-washing.
- **Mantle-only** (chain ID 5000). No other execution chains.
- **Custody safety.** USDC-only deposit; USDY & AUSD via DEX (blocklist-aware),
  never KYC-gated mint; no leverage/looping; ALLOCATOR is a guardrail-bounded hot
  key with a kill switch.
- **Verify addresses on-chain** before integrating. Develop/test against
  `anvil --fork` of Mantle mainnet.
- **Ground-truth reads via RPC** for held assets (Aave position, USDY NAV/DEX price,
  AUSD proof-of-reserves); 1delta is breadth/UX only.
- **Never commit secrets.** Git-ignored `.env` + documented `.env.example`. No
  secret logging.
- **Scope discipline:** Must -> Should -> Could. Keep changes focused; no speculative
  features or premature abstractions.

## Stack (do not substitute without asking)
Solidity + Foundry (forge/anvil/cast) · React + Vite + Tailwind + daisyUI ·
**RainbowKit + wagmi + viem (frontend)** · Node.js + TypeScript + Fastify + **viem
(backend/agent — no ethers)** · Vitest + Forge tests · Docker + Caddy · **Anthropic
API (Claude) via `@anthropic-ai/sdk`** · 1delta API + Mantle RPC.
UI: clean/professional, purple accent (#7c3aed light / #8b5cf6 dark), light+dark
themes — see `docs/ui.md`.

## Conventions
- TypeScript strict mode; no plain JS source files.
- Solidity: explicit visibility, custom errors (not `require("string")`), NatSpec on
  external/public functions, checks-effects-interactions, reentrancy guards on
  fund-moving functions. Prefer OpenZeppelin/Solmate. Match `docs/spec.md` section 2 interfaces.
- Comments explain non-obvious WHY only — never narrate what code does, never leave
  "explaining the change" comments.
- Every fund-moving contract needs Forge fork tests (happy path + guardrail
  violation + depeg/de-risk + liquidity-crunch withdrawal). Risk engine + TS
  validator need Vitest. Frontend follows `docs/ui.md`; build with mock data first.
- Money math: bigint/fixed-point everywhere — no floats for on-chain amounts.
  Always enforce minOut/slippage on swaps.

## Workflow
- **Branches:** `claude/features` (agent), `cursor/<name>` (Cursor). Stay on the
  working branch unless asked.
- **Commits:** one logical change per commit; clear messages.
- **PRs:** **create a GitHub PR after every completed task or logical step.** PR body
  must state what was built and which tests pass. Update the relevant `docs/` file
  if the plan changes.
- **Review:** every PR must pass the checks in `.cursor/rules/pr-review.mdc` before
  merge. Agentic reviewers must use that file as their review checklist.
- Keep `docs/architecture.md` / `docs/spec.md` / `docs/ui.md` / `docs/agents.md` /
  `CLAUDE.md` / `project.mdc` in sync when the plan changes.
- When unsure about guardrails, custody, the 1delta boundary, or scope — ask first.
